Produced by the [resiliency-skills](https://github.com/latent-sre/resiliency-skills) suite. This
repo's CI validates every artifact against the **vendored** schemas in `.sre/schemas/` (pinned to the
engine version that generated it) and runs a fail-closed secret scan.

## Layout

- `metadata/` — criticality, dependencies, deployment, … (neutral artifacts)
- `alerts/intent/` — neutral AlertIntents · `alerts/<tool>/` — rendered tool configs (review before applying)
- `runbooks/` — RunbookSpecs + rendered Markdown
- `slos/`, `dashboards/`, `diagrams/`
- `.sre/` — vendored schemas + engine version pin · `.proposed/` — AI re-proposals for human-edited files

## Reviewing

Nothing here is verified against a live system unless a human checked it. Prioritize `confidence: low`
and `unverified-against-live: true` items, and treat every `REPLACE_ME__…` sentinel as **required
configuration** that must be set deliberately before anything is applied.
